Constructor Detail

AsyncDatabaseWriter

public AsyncDatabaseWriter(String executor,
                           AsyncQueue<E> input,
                           Database database,
                           WriteOperation operation,
                           int commitSize,
                           boolean isCommitEventually)
Creates a new instance that runs in the given executor, consumes items from the given input queue, and writes them to the given database.

Parameters:
executor - If null, uses the default executor.
input - Can't be null.
database - Can't be null.
operation - Can't be null.
commitSize - Number of items to save in a single commit.
isCommitEventually - If true, Database.commitWritesEventually() is used instead of Database.commitWrites().
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - If the given input or database is null.
